  "text": "It is difficult to imagine discourse representation theorists, who argue for the explicit representation in memory of implicit inferences (e.g., [CITATION_1] Meyer, 1974) , arguing that explicit inferences are not represented. In schema theories (e.g., Rumelhart & Ortony, 1977) , explicit discourse information is used to bind schema variables, again suggesting that predictable information would receive explicit mental representation.",
